        <p data-uuid="5420496ddbd145399a9568346f81c085">Greek scientists and mathematicians also gained fame
            for their contributions to geometry and for accurately calculating the size of
            Earth. Doctors studied the human body to understand how it worked. One Greek
            engineering invention that is still used today is a water screw, which brings
            water to farm fields.</p>
