        <p data-uuid="84df044c651b49c39810ba42d393993b">Roman laws were written and kept on public display
            so all people could know them. Roman concepts of equality before the law and
            innocent until proven guilty protected Roman citizens’ rights.<br />
        </p>
        <p data-uuid="3db64c215b60431b8561a8dd3b1f2b27">
            The political ideas of Greece and Rome survived to
            influence governments around the world, including that of the United States. In
            the U.S. political system, citizens vote for representatives, making the nation
            a democratic republic.</p>
